The '''[[University of Texas at Arlington|UT Arlington]] men's basketball team''' is an NCAA Division I [[college basketball]] team competing in the [[Southland Conference]].<ref>[http://www.utamavs.com/sports/m-baskbl/txar-m-baskbl-body.html UT Arlington men's basketball official website]</ref> Home games are played at [[Texas Hall]], located on [[University of Texas at Arlington]]'s campus in [[Arlington, Texas|Arlington]]. The team appeared in the [[2008 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|2008 NCAA tournament]], losing against the #1 seed [[Memphis Tigers|Memphis]] in the first round, although Memphis was later forced to vacate the win due to infractions committed by the program.
UT Arlington will begin competing in the [[Western Athletic Conference]] on July 1, 2012.<ref name="WAC">{{cite web|publisher=[[Fort Worth Star-Telegram]]|title=UTA accepts invitation to WAC|url=http://www.star-telegram.com/2011/07/14/3221759/uta-to-announce-move-to-wac.html|date=2011-07-14|accessdate=2011-07-14}}</ref>
== Team history == The Mavericks are one of the founding teams of the [[Southland Conference]], which began with five institutions on March 15, 1963.<ref>[http://www.southland.org/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=18400&KEY=&ATCLID=945973 Southland Conference History]</ref> Although only 14 of 51 seasons have resulted in an overall winning record, 5 of the past 10 seasons have winning records along with a tie for the 2004 regular season champion and a 2008 conference tournament championship that led to their first NCAA Tournament appearance.<ref>[http://www.utamavs.com/photos/schools/txar/sports/m-baskbl/auto_pdf/0910-mg-pt5-record-book.pdf Media guide record book]</ref>
== Facilities == The Mavericks currently play at [[Texas Hall]], which is a 3,300 seat theater on the campus. The teams play on the stage, and fans can watch the game from either the theater seats or the bleacher section.
A new arena called the [[UT Arlington College Park Center|College Park Center]] with a seating capacity of 6,500 will host the team in 2012.<ref>[http://www.fwbusinesspress.com/display.php?id=9581 UT-Arlington arena long-sought goal for city, school]</ref><ref>[http://www.fwbusinesspress.com/display.php?id=9517 UT-Arlington to build $73 million events facility]</ref> The facility will be located on the eastern side of the campus along with new housing, parking, and retail developments.
== Coaches == The Mavericks have had 7 coaches, listed below, in their 51-year history. [[Scott Cross (basketball coach)|Scott Cross]] is the current coach.
* Tom Tinker - 1959-1966 (7 seasons) * Barry Dowd - 1966-1976 (10 seasons) * Bob LeGrande - 1976-1987 (11 seasons) * Jerry Stone - 1987-1988 (1 season) * Mark Nixon - 1988-1992 (4 seasons) * Eddie McCarter - 1992-2006 (14 seasons) * [[Scott Cross (basketball coach)|Scott Cross]] - 2006âpresent (entering 5th season)
